    <briefdescription>
<para>eSPI out-of-band transaction packet format </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>For Tx packet, eSPI driver client shall specify the OOB payload data and its length in bytes.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>For Rx packet, eSPI driver client shall indicate the maximum number of bytes that can receive, while the eSPI driver should update the length field with the actual data received/available.</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para><simplesect kind="note"><para>In all cases, the <ref refid="structespi__oob__packet_1adf45a10c88a171df8e7138929958b346" kindref="member">len</ref> does not include OOB header size 3 bytes. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
